Jeffery Xiong vs Awonder Liang
U.S. Championship (2020) 
26.10.2020, Round 1

1. Nf3 Nf6 2. d4 g6 3. Nbd2 d5 4. b4 Bg7 5. e3 O-O 6. Be2 c6 7. O-O a5 8. b5 c5 9. c3 Nbd7 10. a4 b6 11. Ba3 Bb7 12. c4 Rc8 13. Rc1 Re8 14. cxd5 Nxd5 15. dxc5 Nxc5 16. Bxc5 bxc5 17. Qb3 Nb6 18. Rfd1 Qc7 19. Nc4 Bd5 20. Nfd2 Red8 21. Qc2 e6 22. Nxa5 Ra8 23. Ndc4 Bxc4 24. Nxc4 Nxa4 25. Bf3 Rxd1+ 26. Rxd1 Ra7 27. Rd6 Nc3 28. b6 Ra1+ 29. Rd1 Nxd1 30. bxc7 Nxe3+ 31. Bd1 Nxc2 32. c8=Q+ Bf8 33. Qd8 Kg7 34. h4 Nd4 35. Ne3 Nf5 36.  h5  Nxe3 37.  fxe3  Ra6 38.  Bb3  Rd6 39.  Qg5  Rd7 40.  Qe5 +  Kg8 41.  Bc4  Rd1 + 42.  Kf2  Rc1 43.  Qf4  Kg7 44.  g4  Be7 45.  Qe5 +  Kg8 46.  Qb8 +  Kg7 47.  Qb2 +

The U.S. Championship is a 12-player round-robin tournament taking place online from 26-29 October 2020 on Lichess. The prize fund is $150,000, with Hikaru Nakamura the favourite to win a 6th US title and the $40,000 top prize.

Players receive 25 minutes for the entire game, plus a 5-second increment starting from move one. A tie for 1st place will be determined by two 10+2 rapid games and, if still tied, an Armageddon game where White has 5 minutes to Black's 4 but a draw counts as a win for Black. Official website: www.uschesschamps.com
